# ─── Supabase (required for backend mode) ────────────────────────────────────
# Get these from: https://supabase.com/dashboard → project → Settings → API
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-here

# OpenAI key is SERVER-SIDE ONLY — never put it in the client bundle.
# Set it in Supabase secrets:  supabase secrets set OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...

# ─── Google Sign In ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. console.cloud.google.com → NEW project "PhysiqueMax" (do not reuse old OAuth clients)
# 2. APIs & Services → OAuth consent screen → External → add your Gmail as Test user
# 3. Credentials → Web application (for Supabase + later web)
#    - Do NOT use auth.expo.io (deprecated, returns Not Found)
# 4. Credentials → iOS application — REQUIRED for Expo Go on iPhone:
#    - Bundle ID: host.exp.Exponent  (not com.physiquemax.ai)
#    - Copy iOS Client ID → EXPO_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_IOS_CLIENT_ID below
# 5. Credentials → iOS application — for App Store build later:
#    - Bundle ID: com.physiquemax.ai
# 6. Supabase → Authentication → Providers → Google → Enable
#    - Client ID + secret = Web client
#    - "Authorized Client IDs" (if shown): add BOTH Web + iOS client IDs
EXPO_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_WEB_CLIENT_ID=your-web-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com
EXPO_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_IOS_CLIENT_ID=your-expo-go-ios-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com
EXPO_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_ANDROID_CLIENT_ID=your-android-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com

# ─── Apple Sign In ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. developer.apple.com → Identifiers → App ID com.physiquemax.ai → Sign In with Apple
# 2. Create Services ID + Key (.p8) for Sign in with Apple
# 3. Supabase → Authentication → Providers → Apple → Enable
#    - Client IDs: com.physiquemax.ai (native) and your Services ID (web)
#    - Secret Key: contents of .p8 + Key ID + Team ID

# ─── Email confirmation (Supabase Auth → URL Configuration) ─────────────────
# Add every redirect URL the app uses (run the app once and check Metro logs, or log
# getEmailAuthRedirectUrl() from src/auth/authRedirect.ts). Examples:
#   physiquemax://auth/callback
#   exp://127.0.0.1:8081/--/auth/callback          (Expo Go on simulator)
#   exp://192.168.x.x:8081/--/auth/callback       (Expo Go on device, LAN)
# Site URL can stay as your production web URL; redirect URLs must include the list above.
#
# Dev tip — avoid "email rate limit" while testing signups:
# Supabase Dashboard → Authentication → Providers → Email → disable "Confirm email".
# Or confirm users manually: Authentication → Users → user → Confirm email.

# ─── Custom AI Backend (replaces GPT-4o for measurement extraction) ───────────
# Deploy ai-backend/ with Docker, then set:
#   EXPO_PUBLIC_AI_BACKEND_URL=https://your-ai-backend.fly.dev
#   EXPO_PUBLIC_AI_BACKEND_KEY=your-api-key   (optional, for auth)
# When set, ALL physique measurement extraction uses the CV/ML pipeline — no GPT.
# The Supabase coaching call (glowUpPrediction, dietary recommendations) still runs.
EXPO_PUBLIC_AI_BACKEND_URL=
EXPO_PUBLIC_AI_BACKEND_KEY=

# ─── App Config ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
EXPO_PUBLIC_APP_ENV=development

# Set to true to skip all network calls and use local mock data instead.
EXPO_PUBLIC_USE_MOCK_API=true
